# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Use loops to traverse through the spaces, alphabet and other characters.
This is done by using **Character.isDigit()** to identify the Digits and then use the **result = result * 10 + digit** to add it to the number.
# Complexity
- Time complexity:**O(n)**
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->


# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int myAtoi(String s) {
        if (s.length() == 0) {
            return 0;
        }
        int i = 0;
        int sign = 1;
        int result = 0;
        while (i < s.length() && s.charAt(i) == ' ') //Skip the Spaces
        {
            i++;
        }
        //The Sign of the Number is calculated
        if (i < s.length() && (s.charAt(i) == '+' || s.charAt(i) == '-')) {
            if(s.charAt(i)=='-')
                sign=-1;
            else
                sign=1;
            i++;
        }
        //Now We find the Number
        while (i < s.length() && Character.isDigit(s.charAt(i))) {
            int digit = s.charAt(i) - '0';
            if (result > (Integer.MAX_VALUE - digit) / 10) {
                if(sign==1)
                    return Integer.MAX_VALUE;
                else
                    return Integer.MIN_VALUE;
            }
            result = result * 10 + digit;
            i++;
        }
        return result * sign;
    }
}

