## JAVA EASY SOLUTION
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
1)Starting we are checking whether the string is null or not.
2)Then to remove the leading white spaces we are using the trim function.
3)Then we are checking the sign of the string . Initially we have taken the sign as +1.if it is negative then we are changing it to
-1.
4)Then we are initialising the index . if there is any sign we will start traversing from 1 else 0 .
5) Now we will traverse till index is less than the length of the string . During the traversing if there is white space or any words we are breaking the loop.
6)now we are converting the ans to the long by ans = ans*10+s.charAt(index)-'0'.
7)Finally checking whether our ans is in the given range or not
8)Finally we typecasting our long ans to int and returning it.

class Solution {
    public int myAtoi(String s) {
        if(s==null)
        {
            return 0;
        }

        s=s.trim();
        if(s.length()==0)
        {
            return 0;
        }
        int sign = +1;
        long ans = 0;
        if(s.charAt(0)=='-')
        {
            sign = -1;
        }
        int MAX = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
        int MIN = Integer.MIN_VALUE ;
        int index = (s.charAt(0)=='+'||s.charAt(0)=='-')?1:0;
        while(index<s.length())
        {
            if(s.charAt(index)==' '||!Character.isDigit(s.charAt(index)))
            {
                break;
            }
            ans = ans*10+s.charAt(index)-'0';
            if(sign==-1&&-1*ans<MIN)
            {
                return MIN;
            }
            if(sign==1 && ans>MAX)
            {
                return MAX;
            }
            index ++;
        }
        return (int)(sign*ans);
    }
}

